<br>
Note to Self: Taking a KoS to CoV cleric into WW is bad, very bad.<br>
<br>
After a few other Misadventures, (I really need to pickup a copy of CR for Dummies), we decide to do this kill <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Mage</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> style and all the non-kos folks start running around Yeldema's nest, reviewing the pathing.  Ironically, the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ranger</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> was the one that suggested this idea, (lord I had to have been tired).<br>
<br>
Long story short, we go in again pull to a beautifully timed pathing location and lay waste to Yeldema.  No Dragonhide Boots...No Talisman...Not even a postcard saying <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;Wish you were here&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->...no.  What drops to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> this</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Magicians pure surprise is a copy of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Burnout IV</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->!<br>
<br>
Just had to share.  Felt really good.  Went to help a good friend get an item she's been dreaming of, and out of blue <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> poof</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> an item drops that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> have been dreaming of.<br>
<br>
